#
ANGALOT

The History of Angalot, Heroic Druid from the Rain Forest

        Many tales of brave and heroic adventurers are told in these days
of thunder. Many tales of struggle for prevail, of treason, of stealth,
murder and sinister plans; but also, stories about strong, brave, 
courageous, and wise ones, those who use the power of their arms and their
minds to ruthlessly fight against evil forces that threaten to eternally
darken the skies above and souls within.
        These tales are told among the common people, and a-many of them
is about one powerful adventurer who fights his way through the cruel
world, seeking for vengeance upon those who made him suffer. But one story
is different of all others; it is told with upper delight and with strange
glinting in the eye, as the character the tale is about is a young and
brave female.
        Once upon a time, there was a small village of gnomes who lived
their merry lives on the edge of a little forest. They were foragers,
lived peacefully and had almost no idea about the meaning of the incoming
news (which weren't many) about the threat that has started to spread
along the country.
It has happened that a troup of savage Orcs was passing near their village
while on a scouting assignment. Gnomes spotted them and, frightened by
their ugly faces, foul stench and big swords, and since they never have
seen anything like them before, thought that Orcs were on their way to
slay them.
Mothers began to run with their children in their arms and with fear in
their eyes, while males stood before the village, trembling, with wooden
clubs in their hands.
Orcs were ruthless and longed for battle, so they slaughtered the entire
village, both men and women, elders and children. Nobody had survived to
warn about the incoming enemy troops.
Actually, there was one survivor, a small baby, a girl named Rineltha.
She would have died there, alone in the forest, in the pool of blood of
her dead mother, if it wasn't for a pair of elves who were friends with
her village and lived nearby. They heard the sounds of battle, and
mourning of wounded, and silence, and they set out to see if there were
any survivors. And they found Rineltha there, at the very brink of her
life...

        Rineltha grew in a nice family, surrounded by love and in direct
contact with Nature. Her foster-parents named her "Angalot", meaning "iron
flower" in high-elven. She grew more beautiful and wise as the years
passed; when, on her 17th birthday, her parents told her everything they
knew about her. Determined as she was, she told them goodbye, as they were
afraid she will do, took a few of her belongings she thought she might use
in the cold outside world and set out to seek revenge...
          
#
ANSI COLOR

If you have a color-capable terminal and wish to see useful color-coding
of information, use the COLOR command to set the level of coloring you see.

> color off
This command disables all color.

> color on
This command enables colors.

You can use these color codes in your PROMPT or in your TITLE:
Color sequence starts with the & character (SHIFT+7) followed by a
color code. Color codes are given below.
                                            
Using color will slow down the speed at which you see messages VERY 
slightly. The effect is more noticable on slower connections.  Even if you 
have color turned on, non-colorized messages will not be slowed down at 
all.

Color codes:

l - &l Black&0
r - &r Red&0
g - &g Green&0
y - &y Yellow &0
b - &b Blue     &0
p - &p Purple (magenta)&0
c - &c Cyan&0
w - &w White (looks grey in normal terminals, use W &Wfor white)&0
0 - &0 Turn the color off&0
You can use big letters for BOLD variants (eg. G is &Gbold green&0).

Other special codes:
u - &u Underline (on Xterminals)
f - &f Flashing text (on normal terminals)
v - &v Reverse mode&0


See also: COLORSPRAY
#
AREAS ZONE WORLD

Use the 'areas' command instead.

See Also: MIDGAARD
#
ARENA CTF

Lands of Myst MUD features a fully funcional "Capture the Flag" arena. The
rules are simple: Players join two teams (RED and BLUE) after the arena has
been opened.  Players are then randomly thrown into the arena maze, ready to
begin with the game. Each team has it's base; RED Team base is always in the
north-west corner, BLUE Team base is in the south-east corner. RED and BLUE
flags are randomly placed in the maze. RED team's job is to capture the BLUE
flag, by bringing it to RED base and typing 'capture' (and vice-versa for
the blue team. If a player dies, he/she will be transfered to a random
location in arena, and fully restored while keeping all the equpment he/she
had. Scoring:
- Killing an enemy team member counts 1 point
- Capturing enemy flag counts 5 points

Winner is the team with higher score after the arena closes.

Players may use 'teamtell' command (shortcut is '', just left of number 1 on
keyboard) to talk to their team members.

usage of ctf command (which starts the arena):
ctf lo hi delay cost length | standard
lo - min level allowed in arena
hi - maximum level allowed in arena
delay - time in mud hours before arena starts
cost - (100-1000) relative cost in coins and quest points to enter arena
length - arena length in mud hours

using option 'standard' will invoke this configuration:
lo: 7
hi: 50
delay: 3
cost: 100
length: 15

NOTICE:
There must be at least 4 players (two on both sides) to start the arena.
#
ASSASSIN HIRE

You can hire assassins for a certain amount of money to do a "job" for you.
You must first seek for a assassin's hideout (there is one in the Zoo for 
example). When in there, type 'list' to get a list of mercenaries and then 
hire <assassin> <victim> to arrange a job. Victim is a player visible to 
you.

#
ASSIST

Usage: ASSIST <person in need>

If Quifael is being beaten senseless by a warg and you feel brave enough
to help him, type ASSIST QUIFAEL to hit the warg.  Note that the warg will
keep hitting Quifael; assist only makes you start to fight whomever you're
trying to assist.

> assist quifael

See also:  RESCUE, FLEE
#
AUTO AUTOEXIT AUTODIR AUTOSAC AUTOLOOT AUTOSPLIT AUTOGRAT AUTOASSIST AUTOSCAN AUTOMAP AUTOSAVE

AUTOEXIT shows a verbose list of available exits at your location.
AUTODIR shows you a brief list of exits that are available at your location.
AUTOSAC allows you to perform the ritual of corpse sacrifice, which will 
disintegrate the dead body of your victim and allow the goodies contained 
within to spill out onto the floor.
AUTOLOOT will allow you to get all the items from your victim when it dies.
AUTOSPLIT will split the looted coins among the members of your GROUP.
AUTOGRAT will congratulate when some player gains a level. 
AUTOASSIST will determine if you'll autoassist your group leader when he/she 
attacks. If you are head of a group it will determine will your pets 
autoassist you.
AUTOSCAN will make you scan whenever you move into a new location.
AUTOMAP shows you a graphical map of your surroundings.
AUTOSAVE will automatically save your character every three minutes.

You can turn everything on by typing auto all, also you can disable it all 
by typing auto none.

See also: TOGGLE
#
AWHO

This commad is exactly like 'who' but shows only players in arena
with some additional information.
#
BANK WITHDRAW DEPOSIT BALANCE CASHCARD

Commands to take money out of the bank, put money in the bank, or see how
much money you have in the bank.  Can be used at any branch of the First
National Bank of (wherever you see an automatic teller machine) or with the 
cashcard.

> deposit 400
> withdraw 1000
> balance
#
BID

Use this command to bid on auction item. Use 'bid more' to match next price.

Example:

> bid 200
> bid more
#
BOARDS

Bulletin boards are the forum of interplayer communication on the MUD.
There are different bulletin boards for different purposes -- for example,
a standard mortal board, a board for immortals, a board for fun "social"
messages, etc.  Naturally, not all players may be allowed to read all
types of boards.

Type "LOOK BOARD" to see the messages already posted on a board.  Type
"WRITE <subject>" to post a message to a board; terminate a message with
a '@' as the first character on a line.  Type "READ <number>" to read a
post.  Type "REMOVE <number>" to remove your own messages.

> look at board
> write Am I using these boards correctly?
[writes the message; terminates with a '@']
> look at board
> read 6
> remove 6
#
BOSS

This command will output a standard unix directory listing on your screen
Handy if you have to hide what you do.
#
BRIEF

Toggle "brief mode".  When in brief mode, you don't see the descriptions of
the room you are in; only the name of the room and the people and objects
there.  Unless you're very familiar with the area in which you're 
travelling, however, it is not advisable to use this command.  Frequently, 
you will find small but vital hints in the descriptions of the rooms: An 
extra peek at your surroundings could mean the difference between life and 
death!

If you explicitly type 'look', you will always see the full room 
description, even in BRIEF mode.

See also: COMPACT, LOOK, DISPLAY, TOGGLE
#
BUG TYPO IDEA

For making useful suggestions to the Powers that Be.

{bug | typo | idea} <text>

> bug the entire game crashes when I type 'put bag in bag'
> idea make a restaurant in Midgaard
> typo 'sence' should be spelled 'sense'
#
BURY DIG

Syntax: dig | bury  <object>

This commands will allow you to dig and bury objects, if it is possible on 
the terrain you are currently standing. Object that is burried can not be 
seen buy anyone, and only digging at that exact location will reveal it.
You won't be able to issue commands sometime after you dig or bury, while 
you aren't finished with it.
#
BUY

If you'd like to purchase an item from a shop and have the money, you can 
buy it.  Items can be bought by name, or by their number in the shop 
listing, and can be bought in quantity.
 
Examples:
 
> buy sword        (buy the first sword on the list)
> buy #3           (buy the third item on the list)
> buy 4.sword      (buy the fourth sword on the list)
> buy 10 bread     (buy 10 pieces of bread)
> buy 10 #2        (buy 10 of the second item on the list)
 
See also: SHOPS SELL LIST VALUE
#
CAST

For "magical" people. If you want to throw a spell at someone or something.
Example : cast 'burning hands' <player>

Note that the name of the spell must be enclosed by "'"s. Each spell will 
use some of your MANA points.

See also : help on each individual spell, for example:
  > help cure ligh
  > help fireball
  > help energy drain
#
CHANNEL AUCTION GOSSIP CHAT BID CHANNELS

These are channels reserved for specific purposes.  Except for Chat, 
Messages on these channels reach everyone who is monitoring them.
Chat only reaches people monitoring the gossip channel and shares your 
race.

auction <item> <price>
gossip <string>
chat <string>

> auction sword 100
> gossip Hey, is that a short sword on your belt or are you happy?

If there is something already on AUCTION you use the BID command to 
participate. You can also type 'auction info' to see what's on auction.


You can use gossip for emotes and socials:

> gossip @is very happy today.
> gossip #pat fido

To find out out what channels you are listening type TOGGLE
See also:  BID SAY GSAY
#
CLAN OUTLAW "BLUE DRAGON" NIGHTSNAKE CLANS

There are 4 clans in the Lands of Myst. There are some common rules of 
engagement you should know of.

   NEWBIE is the basic clan, everyone gots into when they start a new 
character. Newbies can not kill other players, nor can be killed by other 
players. When you reach level 7 you become an OUTLAW. Then you have to 
search for Abrams, enter the Wheel of Destiny room, and have your destiny 
decide your future clan.
   
   BLUE DRAGON and NIGHTSNAKE are two clans that have been in war as far as 
the world exists. As a member of these clans, you enjoy your clan's 
protection and are to slaughter as many of the opposite clan members you 
can. That's it. Simple. You can also freely attack any of the OUTLAWS buy 
may not attack NEWBIES. Also members of thiese clans have the privilege to
own a HOUSE (see help on 'houses' and 'house').

   OUTLAWS aren't actually a clan, rather a bunch of rebels that couldn't 
fit anywhere. You become an OUTLAW in either of the two ways. When you 
reach level 7 you become an OUTLAW but you can decide to choose one of the 
clans. You don't have to do it right away. The second way to become an 
OUTLAW is to be expelled from your clan (either BLUE DRAGON or the 
NIGHTSNAKE). You do that by going to Abrams and typing 'expell'. Once 
expelled, you can not join any clan ever after, and you stay an OUTLAW 
forever. OUTLAWs can attack everyone (except NEWBIEs) and can be attacked 
by everyone. The strongest OUTLAW should be their leader (because he has 
the power of teaching others the lesson *grin*).

See also: CLANLIST, CLANINFO, CTELL, PKSCORE
#
CLANLIST CLANINFO

