#
DEXTERITY INTELLIGENCE WISDOM CONSTITUTION CHARISMA STATS

   Strength measures your pure muscle power. It determines things like how 
much weight you can carry, how big weapons you can wield, your bonus to 
doing damage and so on.
   Intelligence is just that. It will measure how quick you'll be learning 
your skills, your resistance to some magical things. It will also greatly 
affect the destructive power of your spells as well as mana points gain per 
level. In combat, intelligence helps you make critical hits and avoid 
those too.
   Wisdom measures 'the old man with long beard' in you. Depending upon 
this stat, you'll be receiving more or less practice points for your 
skills. It will also affect your mana gain per level as well as some other 
spell-casting matters.
   Dexterity mirrors your reflexes, agility and speed. If you have 
high dexterity, you'll be hitting your opponent more often and accurate, at 
the same time avoiding more blows. It's a general combat attribute.
   Constitution is what decides your combat endurance. High constitution 
character will have much more hit points to tank a combat. This is the most 
important stat for a warriors.
   Charisma measures your control over various situations. If you are high 
on charisma, you have smaller chances of being attacked by an aggressive 
monster, higher resistence to some magic stuff and so.
#
DIAGNOSE

diagnose
diagnose <character>

The DIAGNOSE command tells you how wounded a character looks.  If you are
fighting someone, you can use DIAGNOSE with no arguments to diagnose the
person you're fighting.

> diagnose
> diagnose rasmussen
#
DIE DEAD DYING

When you die few things happen. If your level is higher then level 7 you
will lose quarter of experiance for your level. Also your equipment will
remain in your corpse. Your body is then reborn, and you may start a new
life.
#
DISABLE

Usage: disable <trap name>

After you noticed a trap (or you just have wild guess it is there) you may
try to disable it. Depending on your dexterity, intelligence and knowledge
of that trap you my either succeed or trigger it. Anyone can try their luck
in disabling the trap, but it's best to leave it to professionals.

See also: TRAP
#
DISPLAY

Syntax: display 1 | 0

You can use display command to split your screen and have a status windows 
at the bottom of your screen. It looks really cool if you are having fast 
connection and terminal. Display 1 will turn it on, display 0 will put it 
back to default.

See also: PROMPT
#
DONATE

This command takes an object that you no longer want and deposits it in the
donation room of Midgaard to assist newbies in getting started.  There is
a 75% chance objects donated will wind up in a donation room in Midgaard,
and a 25% chance the item will be junked.

donate <object>
donate <number> coins

> donate shield
> donate all.bread
> donate 500 coins

See also: JUNK
#
DROP

If you lose interest in a carried item, you can drop it on the ground.

drop <item>
drop all.<item>
drop all
drop <number> coins

> drop bottle
> drop all.bread
> drop all
> drop 1000 coins

See also: GET JUNK DONATE
#
DROW

Drow elves, like their surface dwelling cousins, are very
magical in their nature. The difference between the two lay in the fact
that Drow elves left the surface world for a subterranean existence. Drow
tend to dabble more in the "dark" arts of magic, and are evil in their
nature. Some Drow however are outcasts, and have decided to venture out to
the surface.

Drow elves are extremely good spellcasters, and are resistant to magic as
well. They are a lot weaker than humans physically, but compensate with a
greater intelligence. Drow are not as hardy as most races, but are more
dexterous than most as well.

Drow have developed the ability to see in the dark.
#
DRUID

 Druids draw their power from the earth, so their might stems not from dead
magic or capricious gods, but from the lifeforce of the earth itself.
Their abilities in some ways mimic the magical manipulative abilities of
adepts or the god-granted power of the clerics, but they go beyond, dealing
with primal Earthpower itself.
 Although they may not seem formidable in battle, any such preconception
will vanish when druid causes the very earth to open up beneath your feet!
The following skills and multi spells are available to druid:

Level    Skill                        Level    Multi Spell
