DRUNK

Hehe.. You are drunk?
Try getting some smurfberries or having a cleric cure your drunkness.
#
DWARF

Famous for deeds other than the invention of the braided beard and the
double-bladed axe, the Dwarves are known to make fine warriors and 
adventurers.  Strong and hardy, Dwarves also possess a certain innate 
resistance to magic which makes members of this race particularly valuable 
allies and extremely deadly foes.
#
EAT DRINK SIP TASTE

If you're hungry or thirsty, these commands are for you!

> eat bread
> taste bread
> drink from cup
> sip fountain

You can refer to all food you are carrying by 'food' no matter if it's 
waybread, meat or potpie ie. 'eat food', 'put all.food bag'

See also: FILL, POUR
#
EGO "EGO WEAPONS" "EGO ARMORS"

There are many legends of specially crafted weapons and armors, inscribed by
magical runes to give them potent powers and abilities. These items are
called "ego" weapons and armors. Their secret remains unfolded, until they
are identified. Lesser and greater egos exist each with it's own set of
affects. Any weapon or armor can be one of the "ego" ones, so maybe that
crummy sword you are holding is one of the {Bonebreakers}?

You can use 'ego weapons' and 'ego armors' command to list known egos.
#
ELF

This race is a more intelligent and magical race. Most of their
kind live in the forests, depending on the natural resources for their
existence, as well as drawing power from their surroundings to fuel their
magic. Lately, elves have been seen walking around the settlements of the
world using their perceptive abilities and magical natures to some great
effect as the world's secrets are discovered.

Elves are quick-footed, as well as quick of wit. They are also well liked
if not loved by most races as well. Elves lack in strength, and can not
take much punishment in battle; but they are magical in nature and are
excellent spellcasters. In addition to their excellence in the use of
magic, elves are slightly resistant to the effects of magic as well.

Elves all have the ability to see in darkness.
#
EMBALM

Gruber the Embalmer will make useful bags from the skins of dead bodies 
(corpses) you bring him. It's really cool to have a bag made of your worst 
enemy's skin. You can find Gruber in the Midgaard Zoo.
#
EMOTE :

Show people what you're feeling.  The shorthand is ":".

"emote <string>" will display your name, then the string.  For example,
if your name is "Quifael",

> emote is feeling very sad today.

will display:

Quifael is feeling very sad today.

See also: SOCIALS
#
ENGRAVE

You can use engrave command to engrave an item to yourself. After engraving 
it, the item can only be used only by you and it will have a suffix in it's 
name (eg. the long sword of Rassmusen). Other players can pick it but not 
use it. It all costs, and you can also pay (and pay a lot) to unengrave an 
item. For prices and other relevant things, seek Joe's Engraving services 
in the Midgaard Zoo.
#
ENTER

If you type 'enter' while you are outdoors, you'll enter any nearby 
shelter.
You can also follow 'enter' with an argument; for example, 'enter window'.
#
EQUIPMENT

Gives you a list of all the equipment you're wearing, holding, and wielding.

See also: INVENTORY
#
EXAMINE

May give you some valuable information about an item.

See also: LOOK
#
EXITS

Gives you a list of the obvious exits from your location. Of course, the 
less obvious ones won't show up here - you have to THINK in order to locate 
those.
#
EXPERIENCE XP

Whenever you kill a monster or a player, you earn experience points. When
enough experience points are earned, you raise a level.
Things you should know about experience points:
  
  * Every monster is worth some amount of exp. By killing them you gain
    their exp, modified by the level difference between you and the monster.
    If you kill a monster that is lower level then you, you will get less
    exp for it. Also if you kill a higher level monster, you will get extra
    exp.

  * You get experience points for every point of damage you deal.
    
  * You are getting exp for curing and healing someone.

  * See rules about group

See Also: GROUP
#
