help on this topics:

ENGRAVE, EMBALM, HIRE, QUEST, CLAN
#
SPELL SPELLS MANA "SAVING THROW" SAVING_

Spells are ways for spellcasters to express their powers. In order to use
spells, one must spend some of his MANA energy.  Power of all damaging
spells is halved if the victim save a throw versus spell. Furthermore,
SANCTUARY will halve every damage creature is taking, so it will for the
spells. Protection spells (like prot lightning or prot fire) will also lower
the damage taken from corresponding spells. If fire spells are used during
wet conditions (eg. during rain or in water conditions) their damage is also
lowered. Also, intelligence of the caster greatly affects the destructive
power of his spells. At INT of 18 all spells will be casted with 100% power.
Higher INT means more power, lower INT means less.

For list of spells available to your class see help on your class.
    
See also: MAGE CLERIC DRUID
#
SPLIT

Usage:  SPLIT <amount to split>

SPLIT is used to split money among people in your group who are in the same
room as you.  If you are in a group with 4 other people, all of whom are in
the same room with you, and you type SPLIT 100, you will give each of the
other 4 group members 20 coins each.  (100 coins is split 5 ways; you keep
your share and give everyone else their share).

See also: GROUP FOLLOW
#
SPY

  Spying helps a thief character gain information about the world 
around him/her.  After one has typed 'spy', one can look in various 
directions, and given that there is an exit in that direction, and nothing 
blocking the way (like a closed door), then the contents of the other room 
will be displayed.
#
STEAL

Thief Only.

Use steal to steal gold or items from people. The chance of not getting
caught depends on how well you have practiced steal, and if the person
is asleep.

Due to misuse of the steal command, it is now illegal to steal from other
players.  Doing so will get you a flag for your trouble.

Example:

> steal gold drunk

> steal sword mercenary
  (only possible if he is sleeping)

#
STRING

For changing the text-strings associated with objects and characters. The
format is:

string <type> <name> <field> [<string> | <keyword>]

Type is either 'obj' or 'char'.
Field is one of the following(the names may be abbreviated):
Name                  (the call-name of an obj/char - kill giant)
Short                 (for inventory lists (obj's) and actions (char's))
Long                  (for when obj/character is seen in room)
Title                 (for players)
Description           (For look at. For obj's, must be followed by a keyword)
Delete-description    (only for obj's. Must be followed by keyword)

Where a string is expected as the last argument, a newline will make you enter
a string mode, and the game will prompt you for new lines to the string until
you exceed the maximum length for the string or you end a line with a '@'.

Mobiles and objects currently can not be strung.
#
STROM

 	                  STROM'S LOST LANDS

STROM'S LOST LANDS was developed from CircleMUD (3.00bpl8), which was 
developed from DikuMUD (Gamma 0.0).

STROM'S LOST LANDS branched from kosher CircleMUD code by more than 20%.
And thus can be thought of as a derivative of Circle.

STROM'S LOST LANDS was developed by Billy Chan during many lunch breaks
and staying late through the night while working at WindRiver Systems.

I'd like to thank the following people for their help during the development
of STROM'S LOST LANDS:
  
