#
STYLE

This command will change your fighting style. Possible arguments are
"normal", "evasive", "aggresive".
#
THIEF

  The thief is a person which exists alongside society, rather than within, 
or even necessarily without.  The thief lives by skills and cunning, and 
relies on the elements of surprise, trickery, and stealth.

  The prime requisite of thieves is dexterity which makes them very    
slippery opponents. Strength is desirable to make their primary attack,
the backstab, more powerful and to allow them to carry more loot.      
Intelligence is a big plus, allowing them to learn their skills quickly
and expertly as well as to assist their streetsmarts. And as with all  
classes, a hardy constitution will help them survive in the lethal     
dark alleyways and sidestreets of the big cities.                      

SEE ALSO: THIEF ABILITIES
#
THROW

Usage       : throw <direction> <target>              
                                
This allows you to throw something in the direction chosen, aiming the
named target. You must hold or wield an item you want to throw. Order
of throwing is item dual-wielded, item wielded, item held. Thrown objects
will deal damage proportional to their damage dice, or if not weapons, 
to their weight.

If no name is given you will simply fire in that direction, randomly
hitting someone. If name is given, there is still a slight chance you
will miss and hit someone else.

Example:	throw north goblin
See also: QUICKTHROW SHOOT 
#
TIME

Gives you the current game time.  Your initial reaction to the output of
this command may be one of surprise, but you'll get used to it.  You'll
have to, at any rate, since certain things in the game depend on this
particular notion of time; the opening hours of the shops, for example.
#
TITLE

Sets the title people see on the WHO list and when you're in the room with
them.  You can't use parentheses (the "(" and ")" characters) because those
are reserved for flags.

You can use ANSI colors in your title. See help on ANSI.

See also:  FLAGS, ANSI
#
TOGGLE

TOGGLE shows you the current values of various toggles available on the 
MUD.

To change enrage message type 'enrage <mesg>'.
To change grats message type 'grats <mesg>'.
To change prompt see help prompt.

All communication channels are toggled by using 'no' prefix before channel
name.
example:
>nogossip       - toggles gossip channel on/off
>noshout	- toggles shouts on/off

Quest channel toggles automaticaly when you join or leave a quest.

Flags:
Commands to use to toggle flags are
nosumm, nowho, brief, comact, norepeat, color, wimp, nodam, nomisse, nomissf

Actions:
Use 'auto' command to toggle automatic actions.


Additional help files:
	   DISPLAY BRIEF COMPACT AUTO COLOR
           QUEST REPEAT WIMP
           NOINFO NOARENA NOTELL NOSHOUT NOSUMMON NOGRATS NOGOSSIP
	   
#
TOP HALL MOBTOP MOBPK TOPDAM TOPHURT AHALL

These commands show various top-lists.

TOP     - shows top players of the mud, based on their level
HALL    - shows most fameous players of the mud
MOBTOP  - shows most killed mobs
MOBPK   - shows most dangeorus mobs
TOPDAM  - shows most damages players did (also try 'topdam <class>')
TOPHURT - shows most damages players were hurt by (also try 'tophurt <class>')
AHALL   - shows hall of fame for arena
#
TRAIN

There is no old fashioned way training in Land of Myst. Stats are improved
by equipment and spells. Only way to permamently improve one's stat is
having a powerful druid cast 'improve stat' on you.

See help on STAT to learn more.
#
TRAP TRAPS

World hides many dangers, one of them being traps. There are many kind
of traps you can encounter from small damaging darts, over huge constructions
filled with acid, to magical trigger devices such as teleports. So beware
your step!                            

To see traps you know type 'traps'.
To set a trap type 'trap <trap name>'. You may set only one trap per location.
                 
See also: DISABLE
#
TROLL

Trolls are big and slow.  Make that BIG.  Known for their prowess in
battle, their superior physical attributes, and their great size, Trolls
are known to be unsurpassed warriors.  Along with these physical traits
comes a particular dimness of mind and of senses, and Trolls able to cast
spells are rare, and often less than competent.
#
UNGROUP

UNGROUP can be used by group leaders to disband the entire group, or
to kick a specific group member out of the group (and stop him/her from
following the leader).

> ungroup
> ungroup homer

See also: GROUP
#
USE WAND STAFF STAFFS WANDS

Use : Use <Staff>
      Use <Wand> <Target>

Using staff's will automatically target everybody (or everything) in a
room, execpt yourself. Therefore staff's are naturally very powerful, and
yet may be very dangerous to use around other players.

Using wands require that you point it at a target, which can be eihter a
character or an object.

Both staff's and wand's must be HELD in the hand prior to use! (Use the
grab or hold commands). You must still supply the name of the staff or
wand to avoid confusion.
#
VALUE

Before selling an item to a shop, you can ask the shopkeeper how much
he or she is willing to pay for it.

Also, you can value an item in the shopkeeper's inventory to see whether
you can use that item or not.
Example:
 
> value bread
 
See also: SHOPS BUY SELL LIST
